  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA89">
<l>katavik katañciṟanta kañcaṉai muṟkāyn</l>
<l>tatavippōr yāṉai yocittup – pataviyāyp</l>
<l>pāṇiyā ṉīrēṟṟup paṇṭorukāṉ māvaliyai</l>
<l>māṇiyāyk koṇṭilaiyē maṇ</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Once angry with Kaṃsa who was excessive in [his] anger,</l>
<l>hotly attacking the war elephant [and] breaking [its tusk], according to [his]</l>
<l>station<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">pataviyāy poses a problem here. It might go back to an adverbial usage of patavi, “station”, but tradition takes it as a special agent noun based on the noun patavu, “mildness“ (DEDR 3905), that is, “as a mild person”.</note> accepting water with the hand at a former time from Māvali,</l>
<l>did you not<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For this type of negative form cf. Po. 24.3, with further parallels in Po. 34.3 and 79.3.</note>, as a dwarf, take the earth?</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
